Key Match Events: Robbie Brady scored the winning goal in the 88th minute to secure a 2-1 victory for the Republic of Ireland.
The Republic of Ireland came back from a 1-0 deficit to win the match.
Post-Match Reflections: This was the first time since 2011 that the Republic of Ireland had come from behind to win away from home.
Robbie Brady was named Player of the Match for his crucial goal.
